korean:
  title: 송승
  author: 최원우
  language: kor
  text: |-
    재 너머로 가는 우리 스님을 합장하고 보내나니
    봄바람에 지팡이 하나로 들 행장이 가볍구나
    푸른 산 두견새 소리 어디서 들을 것인가
    옛 절의 배꽃에 달이 한창 밝으리라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0530&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Sending Off a Monk
  author: Choe Won-woo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I bow and send off my teacher journeying beyond the ridge.
    With spring breeze and a single staff, his traveling clothes fall light.
    Where shall we hear the cuckoo's call among the green mountains?
    In the ancient temple, pear blossoms bloom beneath the moon's full glow.
  footnotes:
    - The 'ridge' (嶺) refers to a mountain pass, suggesting a journey of departure and spiritual seeking.
    - The cuckoo (杜宇) is a traditional symbol in East Asian poetry representing longing, separation, and the transience of life.
    - Pear blossoms symbolize the fleeting beauty and impermanence central to Buddhist philosophy.
